  "action_required": false,

  "body": "PO chartered thingalog-performance-engineer in Thingalog org 2026-05-27 morning. Scope: direct performance + caching + cost reduction; purely focused on these three concerns (not feature work, not strategy, not security). Position-shape is generalizable — any multi-tenant SaaS substrate org would benefit from the same separation; performance/caching/cost don't fit cleanly under existing canonical role-shapes (engineer = ship features; strategist = plan; security-tester = threats; PM = synthesis). Single derivation; premature for canonical promotion per typical 'third re-derivation = promotion-safe' threshold. File-and-watch. Re-trigger criteria: second SaaS substrate org charters similar position; performance/cost concerns become substantive in OAGP-org itself; multiple re-derivations of same separation justify promotion. Local charter at s:/projects/thingalog/roles/thingalog-performance-engineer.body.md + entry in thingalog org charter recommended_roles. If canonical performance-engineer roledef lands at roledef.org someday, Thingalog migrates local→canonical reference (same pattern as senior-project-oriented-software-engineer + blackhat-tester).",
  "body_ref": "2026-05-27-1000--thingalog-strategist--orgdef-strategist--new-position-chartered-thingalog-performance-engineer-as-canonical-roledef-candidate.body.md",

